02/05/2011
TIRANA, Albania -- Workers and the unemployed staged a protest Sunday (May 1st) to mark international Labour Day. 
Miners rallied in front of the Ministry for Economy seeking better working conditions and better pay, while a group of taxi drivers protested on Tirana's main boulevard demanding that authorities control the market and stop unfair competition from unregistered drivers. 
A rally against unemployment was also held in the eastern town of Korca. 
(Shekulli, Balkan Web, Top Channel - 01/05/11)
